1
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:14,280
You don't need to go deep in the mountains for lingzhi.

2
00:01:14,719 --> 00:01:16,680
There might be some near the ancient tree.

3
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,359
Something's wrong with this tree.

4
00:01:24,599 --> 00:01:25,239
What's wrong with it?

5
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,200
This is a famous internet hotspot.

6
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,879
Lots of people come just to hug it.

7
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,519
There's Gummosis at the base of the trunk.

8
00:01:41,159 --> 00:01:41,599
Come on.

9
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:42,959
Help me hang this up.

10
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:44,959
Are you crazy?

11
00:01:45,159 --> 00:01:46,040
This is the ancient tree king!

12
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:47,840
The elders will kick you out if they see this.

13
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,760
It's sick.

14
00:01:49,879 --> 00:01:51,560
I'm giving it nutrient solution as emergency care.

15
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:52,640
Hurry.

16
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,040
Sick?

17
00:01:58,439 --> 00:01:58,840
Hang it there.

18
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,919
This tree is lacking nutrients,

19
00:02:15,919 --> 00:02:16,759
which is causing it to age

20
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,800
and develop Gummosis.

21
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:20,080
I thought you were going to hurt it earlier.

22
00:02:20,639 --> 00:02:21,879
You really think that's possible?

23
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,560
By rights,

24
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,520
it should be fertilized every year

25
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:27,879
to strengthen the tree

26
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,199
and boost its resistance.

27
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:32,159
That's Dr. Meiduo for you.

28
00:02:32,439 --> 00:02:34,400
You know the stars above and the trees below.

29
00:02:34,439 --> 00:02:35,280
Kudos to you.

30
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:36,840
Stop being a smart aleck.

31
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,240
Let's hurry up the mountain.

32
00:02:43,719 --> 00:02:44,759
Watch your step.

33
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:46,560
There's a wild boar wallow around here.

34
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,599
It's full of mud pits.

35
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:49,639
Step in and you can't pull your leg out.

36
00:02:50,159 --> 00:02:51,840
This way. The ground's firmer here.

37
00:02:53,199 --> 00:02:54,680
How can you tell the way without signs?

38
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:57,080
Don't tell me your Super hearing

39
00:02:57,319 --> 00:02:58,360
has gotten even better?

40
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,240
There's no Super hearing.

41
00:03:02,439 --> 00:03:03,479
Whichever way the wind blows,

42
00:03:03,719 --> 00:03:04,960
that's the way the moss grows.

43
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,280
Give it a pinch,

44
00:03:07,159 --> 00:03:07,800
take a sniff,

45
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:09,840
and you'll find your way.

46
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,280
Let me show you something good.

47
00:03:16,479 --> 00:03:16,919
What is it?

48
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,120
We're here.

49
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:18,919
This is it?

50
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:20,639
What is this thing?

51
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,879
Look. What is this?

52
00:03:23,199 --> 00:03:24,680
This... this is Tianma, right?

53
00:03:25,479 --> 00:03:27,039
Yes, it's Tianma.

54
00:03:27,039 --> 00:03:27,719
Dig it up.

55
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,599
What are you two doing?

56
00:03:31,599 --> 00:03:33,319
Who are you? Mind your own business.

57
00:03:34,439 --> 00:03:36,039
Digging up wild plants is illegal.

58
00:03:36,319 --> 00:03:37,680
If you two keep digging,

59
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,560
I'll film you and post it online.

60
00:03:39,759 --> 00:03:40,319
Hand that over.

61
00:03:40,879 --> 00:03:41,560
Stop!

62
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:44,439
What are you doing?

63
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,360
This is our village's protected forest.

64
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,599
No random digging is allowed.

65
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:49,080
Who do you think you're scaring?

66
00:03:49,879 --> 00:03:50,280
Come here.

67
00:03:50,599 --> 00:03:51,199
Take a good look.

68
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:54,319
What you were about to dig up is wild Tianma.

69
00:03:55,759 --> 00:03:58,159
Tianma is a National Class II Protected Plant.

70
00:03:58,479 --> 00:04:00,719
Poaching and selling it are illegal.

71
00:04:00,719 --> 00:04:01,599
You could face criminal charges.

72
00:04:03,879 --> 00:04:05,000
Forget it, forget it. Let's go.

73
00:04:10,159 --> 00:04:11,080
Thanks for earlier,

74
00:04:11,439 --> 00:04:12,280
for helping us stop them.

75
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:13,639
It was nothing.

76
00:04:14,159 --> 00:04:14,919
And you are?

77
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,240
You two are from the village down the hill?

78
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,079
I'm Nana.

79
00:04:22,439 --> 00:04:24,240
The Commerce Bureau brought me from Guangdong

80
00:04:24,319 --> 00:04:25,319
as an e-commerce instructor.

81
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,439
I just arrived and was looking around.

82
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:28,439
It's quite beautiful here.

83
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:29,800
Yeah.

84
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,800
Lots of tourists come to our village now.

85
00:04:32,399 --> 00:04:32,720
Oh, by the way,

86
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,439
I'm Meiduo, and he's Zhaxi.

87
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,879
We're from Peach Blossom Village down below.

88
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,000
Peach Blossom Village?

89
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,360
I'm staying there too.

90
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,759
At Flower Melody B&B.

91
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,519
Flower Melody B&B is run by my family!

92
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,600
What a coincidence.

93
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,480
What a sacrilege!

94
00:04:49,839 --> 00:04:51,279
Who turned our king tree

95
00:04:51,279 --> 00:04:52,720
into this state?

96
00:04:53,439 --> 00:04:54,319
What are we going to do?

97
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,079
Right?

98
00:04:55,279 --> 00:04:56,279
It was perfectly fine yesterday.

99
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,000
Why is this thing hanging on it?

100
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,240
This is desecrating the Sacred Tree.

101
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,199
There'll be retribution.

102
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:00,920
What do we do now?

103
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,920
Who did this?

104
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:02,519
Exactly.

105
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:03,199
They'll face retribution.

106
00:05:03,839 --> 00:05:04,800
Stop guessing, everyone.

107
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:07,079
You shouldn't go over there.

108
00:05:07,079 --> 00:05:08,600
If you start talking about Gummosis,

109
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,600
and this disease or that disease,

110
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,600
they won't understand.

111
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:11,600
But they...

112
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,439
Let me handle it.

113
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,279
Why is everyone gathered here?

114
00:05:17,279 --> 00:05:17,680
Everything's fine.

115
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,519
Don't scare yourselves.

116
00:05:19,959 --> 00:05:22,199
Zhaxi, look, what is this?

117
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:24,160
And there's a hole drilled here.

118
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:24,800
Yeah.

119
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:26,759
Auntie Baima,

120
00:05:27,199 --> 00:05:28,800
last month at your hospital checkup,

121
00:05:28,959 --> 00:05:30,480
did the doctor draw blood from you?

122
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,319
Yes, they did.

123
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,360
Did it hurt?

124
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,319
It did. My arm went numb.

125
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,319
And did you yell at the doctor?

126
00:05:36,639 --> 00:05:37,879
You little rascal.

127
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:39,439
The doctor was treating me,

128
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:40,279
saving my life.

129
00:05:40,279 --> 00:05:42,199
Why would I yell at them?

130
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:43,319
Exactly my point.

131
00:05:43,519 --> 00:05:44,519
People need checkups,

132
00:05:44,519 --> 00:05:45,720
and so do trees.

133
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:47,000
Trees need checkups?

134
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:47,560
That's right.

135
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,920
We check if it has any chronic issues,

136
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,480
and if it's lacking nutrients.

137
00:05:51,839 --> 00:05:53,920
This hole is to treat the tree,

138
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,079
not to damage it.

139
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:55,959
Look here.

140
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,920
This is like hooking it up to an IV,

141
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,040
giving it nutrient solution.

142
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,720
It even gets an IV drip?

143
00:06:00,959 --> 00:06:01,519
That's right.

144
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:02,319
Auntie,

145
00:06:02,639 --> 00:06:04,839
this stuff costs more than skincare.

146
00:06:05,199 --> 00:06:06,279
If you really wanted to vandalize,

147
00:06:06,519 --> 00:06:07,759
who'd splurge on this?

148
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,120
When it comes to treating trees,

149
00:06:10,279 --> 00:06:11,319
Zhaxi really knows his stuff.

150
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,399
Let's not make a fuss.

151
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,360
If that's the case,

152
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,480
then everyone, let's break it up.

153
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,519
Break it up, break it up.

154
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:16,439
It's nothing, nothing at all.

155
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:27,279
Good thing you thought of the blood test idea.

156
00:06:27,519 --> 00:06:29,040
Otherwise, with all those technical terms,

157
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:29,920
they wouldn't understand.

158
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,040
You're exactly the same as when we were kids.

159
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,079
Always so good at talking your way out.

160
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,040
But thank you, really.

161
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,120
You two keep chatting.

162
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:47,639
As for me,

163
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:48,639
I'll go look around.

164
00:06:49,279 --> 00:06:49,920
Stay safe!

165
00:06:50,279 --> 00:06:51,000
You be careful too.

166
00:06:51,439 --> 00:06:51,839
Bye.

167
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:00,519
Hello?

168
00:07:00,519 --> 00:07:00,920
Nana.

169
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,439
That shop review video last week,

170
00:07:02,439 --> 00:07:03,800
the views dropped by half.

171
00:07:04,079 --> 00:07:05,279
The brand isn't happy.

172
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,279
The final payment got withheld.

173
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:07,319
But that was just an accident.

174
00:07:07,759 --> 00:07:08,800
This time in Linzhi, it's different.

175
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,279
Peach Blossom Village brings its own traffic.

176
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,199
Plus, I'm here as an instructor.

177
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,600
Instructor?

178
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,800
Give me a break.

179
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:16,240
As for your commercial value,

180
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:16,959
don't you have a clue?

181
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,879
If this week's livestream's

182
00:07:18,879 --> 00:07:19,319
GMV (total order value)

183
00:07:19,319 --> 00:07:19,839
doesn't go up,

184
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,839
forget about next quarter's signing fee.

185
00:07:22,079 --> 00:07:22,439
But...

186
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:23,839
No buts.

187
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:26,680
Nana,

188
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,120
your credit card bill's due in days, right?

189
00:07:30,079 --> 00:07:30,759
Figure it out yourself.

190
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:42,959
So cute!

191
00:07:44,199 --> 00:07:45,279
Hello there.

192
00:07:45,279 --> 00:07:46,199
Don't touch it.

193
00:07:46,519 --> 00:07:47,399
Watch out, it'll bite you.

194
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,319
It's wary of strangers.

195
00:07:49,639 --> 00:07:50,560
Is it yours?

196
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,360
It's the village's.

197
00:07:57,079 --> 00:07:58,120
Is this pulu?

198
00:07:58,879 --> 00:07:59,759
You know about pulu?

199
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,319
Can I take a look?

200
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,199
You can tell this isn't machine-made.

201
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:09,920
It's hand-woven, right?

202
00:08:12,319 --> 00:08:13,199
Can you sell it to me?

203
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:14,800
You like it?

204
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,439
It's not for sale.

205
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:19,759
Why not?

206
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,199
If you really like it,

207
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:22,519
I can teach you how to weave one.

208
00:08:22,959 --> 00:08:23,920
Teach me?

209
00:08:25,439 --> 00:08:26,439
You're the instructor who came to the village

210
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:27,879
to give us e-commerce training, right?

211
00:08:28,959 --> 00:08:31,040
You teach us how to sell things,

212
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,360
and I'll teach you how to weave a belt.

213
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:33,639
Fair enough.

214
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:39,600
Let's go.

215
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:43,080
I'm Zhuoma.

216
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:48,120
Come on.

217
00:08:49,799 --> 00:08:51,080
A wild queen.

218
00:08:57,759 --> 00:08:59,120
I look more like a tourist.

219
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,159
Nana!

220
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,080
Nana!

221
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,399
It's really you!

222
00:09:16,559 --> 00:09:17,639
I'm from the B&B.

223
00:09:17,639 --> 00:09:18,559
My name is Sun Qianqian.

224
00:09:18,879 --> 00:09:19,840
I'm such a big fan of yours!

225
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,559
I watch every single one of your videos.

226
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:22,720
Thank you.

227
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,519
The Commerce Bureau told us long ago.

228
00:09:24,519 --> 00:09:25,600
They said they'd invited a top expert

229
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,679
to train the villagers in e-commerce.

230
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,279
You've settled in already, right?

231
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:30,440
Are you comfortable here?

232
00:09:30,639 --> 00:09:32,600
You've got our very best room.

233
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,360
Open the window and there's Namjagbarwa Peak.

234
00:09:34,519 --> 00:09:35,720
The weather's just not great right now.

235
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,480
You could see it earlier when the sun was out.

236
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,399
Thank you.

237
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:39,960
You're welcome.

238
00:09:40,519 --> 00:09:41,879
Where did you wander off to?

239
00:09:41,879 --> 00:09:43,200
I was looking all over for you.

240
00:09:43,639 --> 00:09:44,399
Just taking a stroll.

241
00:09:44,399 --> 00:09:45,840
Taking a stroll without telling me?

242
00:09:46,039 --> 00:09:47,360
What if you got lost?

243
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:51,000
Isn't there just one road in your village?

244
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,039
Now that you mention it, yeah.

245
00:09:54,519 --> 00:09:55,559
But you just got here.

246
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:56,600
I was just worried...

247
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,279
Worried about what?

248
00:09:57,399 --> 00:09:58,120
Worried you'd be bored!

249
00:09:59,080 --> 00:09:59,960
You sure worry a lot.

250
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:00,919
I have to!

251
00:10:00,919 --> 00:10:02,039
You're my idol.

252
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,559
Your idol doesn't need you to worry.

253
00:10:03,559 --> 00:10:04,840
Idols need even more looking after!

254
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:06,399
What if you get worn out?

255
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:09,039
Are you tired?

256
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,600
I'm not tired. I'm young.

257
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,519
Let me tell you, it's our Peach Blossom Festival,

258
00:10:15,799 --> 00:10:17,000
and the peach blossoms are in full bloom.

259
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,480
You can only see peach blossoms beneath snow mountains here.

260
00:10:20,159 --> 00:10:22,320
How long has your B&B been open?

261
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,399
For many years now.

262
00:10:23,399 --> 00:10:25,360
Zhaxi and Uncle Jimei opened it together.

263
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:27,879
Jimei?

264
00:10:29,559 --> 00:10:30,440
He's our head chef.

265
00:10:30,679 --> 00:10:31,320
From Guangdong.

266
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,639
His cooking is amazing.

267
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,679
You'll get to try his cooking tonight.

268
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,799
Nana, what are you looking at?

269
00:10:41,879 --> 00:10:43,159
Nothing. Let's go.

270
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:46,240
Look, that's Namjagbarwa Peak.

271
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,960
Usually, when the sun

272
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,080
shines down on the snow mountain,

273
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,360
it becomes the Golden Mountain at sunrise.

274
00:10:50,559 --> 00:10:52,120
Many people come just to see it.

275
00:10:52,279 --> 00:10:54,320
Nine out of ten visitors never get to see it.

276
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,320
But I think you're a truly blessed person.
